
List
* Ordered collection of items that is mutable (changeable). 
* Allow duplicate members and can store mixed data types.
* list = ['apple', 'banana']
* Lookup time = O(n)

Tuple
* ordered collection of items that is immutable (unchangeable after creation). 
* Allow duplicate members.
* tuple = ('apple', 'banana')
* Lookup time = O(n)

Set
* Unordered collection of unique elements. 
* They are mutable, but do not support indexing.
* set = {1, 2, 3}
* Lookup time is O(1)

Distionary
* An unordered collection that stores data as key-value pairs. 
* Keys must be unique and immutable. Dictionaries are mutable.
* dict = {'name': 'Alice', 'age': '30'}
* Lookup time for a key is O(1)

